title: Spettigue squashes competition at Brandon Open
text:
Spettigue squashes competition at Brandon Open By: Uncredited Report Error 
Tom Spettigue of Shilo shocked a lot of people at the Brandon Open squash tournament at Peak Performance Athletics. 
Some Winnipeggers didn’t attend the event on the weekend figuring they wouldn’t see much competition, but Spettigue never lost a match en route to the A/B mixed open title. In addition to the title, Spettigue earns the opportunity to represent Brandon’s club at Manitoba Squash Pro Series events this year. 
Meanwhile, Lorie Stutsky defeated fellow Brandonite Gail Feser in the C/D mixed open division final to take that crown. Rodman Batson claimed the consolation final.
